# Assets Investment Securities Amount

## identifier
de15000

## type
float

## definition
This is the value of all investment securities which are securities purchased with the intent that they be held to maturity or held for a period of time though not necessarily to maturity this covers equity securities where it is not technically possible to hold to maturity.
These are securities that are not trading securities as defined in accounting standards AASB 139 Financial Instruments: Recognition and Measurement.

## syntax
### xbrl
- balance=debit
- name=Assets.Investment.Securities.Amount
- classification=baf/bafpo/bafpo7.02.26
- period=instant
